<p>How do I run a console controller action from another console controller action?</p>  <p>I've tried the following</p>  <pre><code>class FooController extends Controller {     public function actionBar()     {         $this-&gt;run('baz/quux', ['baz'=&gt;'quux']);     } }  class BazController extends Controller {     public function actionQuux($baz)     {         // ...     } } </code></pre>  <p>I'm getting an error</p>  <blockquote>   <p>Error: Unknown option: --baz</p> </blockquote>  <p>Though the <code>quux</code> action of the <code>baz</code> controller has the <code>baz</code> parameter and running <code>./yii baz/quux quux</code> succeeds.</p>  <p>I don't mean to specify an option, I don't even use options. I want to specify the action's parameter. What should be the format of the parameters array?</p>